Label: HLA-A allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-A gene that is involved in immune responses and histocompatibility processes.

Label: HLA-A wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-A wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, A-1 alpha chain protein, is involved in immune system peptide presentation.

Label: HLA-B allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-B gene that  plays a role in both immune responses and histocompatibility processes.

Label: HLA-B wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for HLA-B wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, B-7 alpha chain protein, plays a role in peptide presentation by the immune system. Certain allelic variants of the HLA-B gene are associated with susceptibility to ankylosing spondylitis, carbamazepine-induced Stevens-Johnson syndrome and allopurinol-induced severe cutaneous adverse reaction.

Label: HLA-C allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-C gene that plays a role in both immune responses and histocompatibility processes.

Label: HLA-C wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-C wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, Cw-1 alpha chain protein, plays a role in antigen presentation and the immune response.

Label: HLA-DPA1 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DPA1 gene that is involved in the regulation of both cellular immune responses and antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DPA1 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DPA1 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 16 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DP alpha chain protein, is involved in the modulation of antigen presentation and T-cell mediated immunity. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

Label: HLA-DPB1 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DPB1 gene that plays a critical regulatory role in antigen presentation and peptide binding specificity.

Label: HLA-DPB1 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DPB1 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 24 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DP(W4) beta chain protein, is involved in the modulation of antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DQA1 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DQA1 gene that plays a role in antigen presentation and immunoregulation.

Label: HLA-DQA1 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DQA1 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 6 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DQ alpha chain protein, plays a role in antigen presentation and the regulation of the immune response. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

Label: HLA-DQB1 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for human HLA-DQB1 gene that is involved in the mediation of antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DQB1 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DQB1 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DQ beta 1 chain protein, plays a role in the regulation of antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DRA allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DRA gene that plays a role in antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DRA wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DRA wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 5 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DR alpha chain protein, is involved in the mediation of antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DRB1 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information on the HLA-DRB1 gene, which is involved in immunoregulation and antigen presentation. The gene has several hundred alleles and polymorphism typing is routinely performed for bone marrow and kidney transplantation.

Label: HLA-DRB1 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DRB1 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 11 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB1-4 beta chain protein, plays a role in the mediation of antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DRB3 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DRB3 gene that is involved in immunoregulation and antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DRB3 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DRB3 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 13 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB3 beta chain protein, is involved in the mediation of antigen presentation and stimulation of the immune response. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

Label: HLA-DRB4 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DRB4 gene that plays a role in both antigen presentation and the regulation of T-cell-mediated immunity.

Label: HLA-DRB4 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DRB4 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 15 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB4 beta chain protein, plays a role in the regulation of antigen presentation. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

Label: HLA-DRB5 allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information for the HLA-DRB5 gene that is involved in the regulation of T-cell-mediated immunity and antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-DRB5 wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-DRB5 wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 13 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DRB5 beta chain protein, is involved in the modulation both of antigen presentation and the immune response. The gene is polymorphic and typing is often performed to determine histocompatibility for hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

Label: HLA-E allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information for HLA-E gene.

Label: HLA-E wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information on human HLA-E  allele which is located in the vicinity of 6p22.1. This allele encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, alpha chain E protein.

Label: HLA-F allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information for HLA-F gene that is involved in the presentation of cytoplasmic protein fragments to cytotoxic lymphocytes.

Label: HLA-F wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-F wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity of 6p21.3 and is approximately 16 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, alpha chain F protein, plays a role in antigen presentation.

Label: HLA-G allele information
SubClass Of: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information for HLA-G gene that is involved in antigen processing and presentation.

Label: HLA-G wild type allele information
definition: Wild type allele information for human HLA-G wild-type allele that is located in the vicinity 6p21.3 and is approximately 4 kb in length. This allele, which encodes HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, alpha chain G protein, plays a role in MHC class I-mediated immune responses.

Label: MHC Class I allele information
definition: Allele information on a family of genes that encode major histocompatibility complex proteins and are involved in the presentation of cytoplasmic protein fragments to cytotoxic lymphocytes.

Label: MHC Class II allele information
definition: Allele information for a family of genes expressed mainly by antigen presenting cells that encode major histocompatibility complex proteins and are involved in the presentation of fragments from phagocytized extracellular proteins to cytotoxic lymphocytes.

Label: Major Histocompatibility Complex allele information
definition: Allele information for gene that is on a group of linked loci, collectively termed H-2 complex in the mouse and HLA complex in humans, that codes for cell-surface histocompatibility antigens and is the principal determinant of tissue type and transplant compatibility.

Label: human MHC class I allele information
definition: Allele information located at human MHC class I locus.

Label: human MHC class II allele information
definition: Allele information located at human MHC class II locus.
